article.headline: Weber State 73, Montana State 60
article.story:
OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Becky O'Neil scored 24 points Saturday to
lead Weber State to a 73-60 victory over Montana State.

Montana State (7-13, 1-6 Big Sky) led 14-13 on a layup by Kati
Burrows, but O'Neil answered with a layup with 12 minutes remaining
in the half and the Wildcats (14-6, 5-2) never trailed again.

Weber State led 38-31 at halftime, but the Bobcats got within
53-51 with 9:50 remaining.

The Wildcats used an 18-2 run to pull away.

Julie Gjertsen added 13 points and nine rebounds for Weber,
while Brooke Hansen had 12 points and Sheila Robertson 11 points
and eight assists.

Hillary Scott led MSU with 32 points and five steals while
Jaimey Tanner added 11 points. Burrows finished with eight points,
half her season average.
